					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Piller set up in the inner, <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Mahaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Aḷupēndra alias Oḍḍamarāja 1235 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to refer to the reign of Oḍḍamarā • • • • • Vallabhāḷupa, the Āḷupa king. It states that Dēvara Mukkaṇṇoḍeya was administering Oḍḍarase when a gift of fifty <hi rend="italic">gadyāṇas</hi> was made probably to a deity. The details are, however, lost.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Manmatha, Kanne (Kanyā) 13, Monday.</hi> On palaeographical grounds the record can be assigned to the 13th century and the details equated to <hi rend="bold">1235 A.D., September 10,</hi> which appears to be the intended date.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
